# P1 Findings

## P1-001 — `FindingPersister` swallows per-finding errors without exposing partial failure

### Area

`packages/thalamus/src/services/finding-persister.service.ts`

### Current behavior

Persistence errors are logged per finding and the loop continues. The method returns only `storedCount`.

### Problem

The parent cycle can be marked completed even if several findings failed to persist. This is resilient but weakly auditable.

### Required fix

Return a richer result:

```ts
interface PersistResult {
  storedCount: number;
  failedCount: number;
  failures: Array<{ title: string; message: string }>;
}
```

Then let `ThalamusService.runCycle()` mark the cycle as completed with warnings or partial persistence metadata.

### Acceptance criteria

* Failed findings are returned to caller.
* Cycle logs include failed count.
* Tests cover partial persistence.

