## P1-009 — Vector driver parsing can produce silent invalid vectors

### Area

`packages/db-schema/src/schema/_vector.ts`

### Current behavior

```ts
fromDriver(value: string): number[] {
  return value.slice(1, -1).split(",").map(Number);
}
```

### Problem

Unexpected formats can produce `[NaN]` or malformed vectors silently.

### Required fix

Make parsing defensive and fail on non-finite values.

Suggested implementation:

```ts
fromDriver(value: string | null): number[] {
  if (!value) return [];
  const inner = value.startsWith("[") && value.endsWith("]")
    ? value.slice(1, -1)
    : value;

  if (!inner.trim()) return [];

  const parsed = inner.split(",").map(Number);
  if (parsed.some((x) => !Number.isFinite(x))) {
    throw new Error("Invalid vector driver value");
  }

  return parsed;
}
```

### Acceptance criteria

* Tests cover empty string, null, malformed vector, valid vector.
* Malformed vector does not return `[NaN]`.

